My heart breaks for #dauntewright his mother, his young son and his entire family. No mother should have to experience what she did on the other end of the phone. 💔 If you’re able, please consider donating to the fund that has been set up to help support Daunte’s family. Please remember that silence is compliance #blacklivesmatter  Link below🙏🏼🕊XoRZ 

https://www.gofundme.com/f/dauntewright

Repost from @meredithmelling
•
It’s heartbreaking to watch Katie Wright, the mother of Daunte Wright, painfully detail her final words with her 20 year old son who called her in fear (rightfully) when he was pulled over by police for a traffic violation and murdered just moments later by one of the officers. Katie Wright will never see her son alive again. This Mother’s Day, I will be donating to The Daunte Wright Sr. Memorial Fund. All funds raised will go towards covering costs related to funeral and burial expenses, mental health and grief counseling, support for Daunte’s son, Daunte Wright Jr., and the Wright family’s fight for justice. Please visit the link in my bio if you’d like to join me in donating. #justicefordauntewright #blacklivesmatter

node.text: 9.11.2001 💔 All I can see are the faces of so many beautiful lives taken and the loved ones who lost them. 🙏🏻 20 years later that horrific moment and the clear view of the falling towers from my west village apartment is as vivid now as it was then. I will never ever forget this unfathomable day and my deepest love for the resilient people of #NYC. My heart goes out to all of those grieving today and always. ❤️ #remember #neverforget #september11
